fields.name: authority
docs: Must sign any changes to discount rates

docs: Addresses of the mint for the tokens being discounted.

fields.name: discountRates
docs: Discount rates. Aligns with indexes of `mint_address` above, so index 0 is for the mint at
index 0, and so forth.
Pass rates with a common denom of 10,000. A rate of 90% (9000) means that
the token will be valued at (90%) = 90% of its face value. If the token was worth $50, it
would now be worth $45 for liquidation and collateral purposes.
TODO should rates be limited to <1? E.g. is it desirable to allow a bonus for some tokens?

fields.name: feeNoteVault
docs: The account with custody of the notes generated from collected fees

fields.name: dexSwapTokens
docs: The account for storing quote tokens during a swap

fields.name: dexOpenOrders
docs: The account used for trading with the DEX

fields.name: dexMarket
docs: The DEX market account that this reserve can trade in

fields.name: discountRate
docs: Discount rate for the token this reserve uses, updated from the common discounts account

fields.name: discountRateVersion
docs: Current version of the discount rate. If lower than the version in the discounts account,
should be updated.

fields.name: haltState
docs: Indicates if the reserve has halted borrows, repays, or deposits:
0 (0b00000000) = nothing halted,
1 (0b00000001) = deposits halted,
2 (0b00000010) = borrows halted,
4 (0b00000100) = repays halted,
8 (0b00001000) = withdraws halted
Allows addition or bitwise AND to combine multiple states:
(e.g., 4 + 2 = 6 (0b00000110) = borrows and repays halted, others allowed)

fields.name: withdrawalTime
docs: Earliest timestamp after which rewards for this distribution can be claimed.
Equivalent to the start of the period + the `min_withdrawal_duration`.
Defaults to 0 if RewardState is not initialized for period.

fields.name: unclaimedRewardUnits
docs: Total amount of unclaimed reward points for this distribution period.
This value is denominated in reward_unit_decimals.
Defaults to 0 if RewardState is not initialized for period.

fields.name: period
docs: Non-authoritative period of this RewardState. Matches index in MarketReward.states array.
Defaults to 0 if RewardState is not initialized for period.

fields.name: info
docs: Info field has to be defined after N*32 bytes from start of RewardState to be
aligned correctly.

fields.name: marketReward
docs: Pubkey of MarketReward account.

fields.name: initialRewardIndexTimestamp
docs: Timestamp at which first reward distribution period index begins.
The first reward period ends at `initial_reward_index_timestamp` + `distribution_period`
This should not change after initialization.

fields.name: distributionPeriod
docs: Length of each distribution period in seconds.
This should not change after initialization.

fields.name: rewardPointsPerPeriod
docs: Reward points allocated across whole market for each distribution period.

fields.name: totalRewardMultiplier
docs: Sum of reward multipliers across all Reserves in the market on each ObligationSide.

fields.name: minWithdrawalDuration
docs: Time in seconds from start of period, after which withdrawal of rewards is allowed.
Typically this is earlier than the end of the period.

fields.name: rewardUnitDecimals
docs: Number of decimal places for cumulative reward units.

fields.name: reserved0
docs: Unused space

types.name: ReserveConfig
docs: We have three interest rate regimes. The rate is described by a continuous,
piecewise-linear function of the utilization rate:
1. zero to [utilization_rate_1]: borrow rate increases linearly from
[borrow_rate_0] to [borrow_rate_1].
2. [utilization_rate_1] to [utilization_rate_2]: borrow rate increases linearly
from [borrow_rate_1] to [borrow_rate_2].
3. [utilization_rate_2] to one: borrow rate increases linearly from
[borrow_rate_2] to [borrow_rate_3].
Interest rates are nominal annual amounts, compounded continuously with
a day-count convention of actual-over-365. The accrual period is determined
by counting slots, and comparing against the number of slots per year.

fields.name: utilizationRate1
docs: The utilization rate at which we switch from the first to second regime.

fields.name: utilizationRate2
docs: The utilization rate at which we switch from the second to third regime.

fields.name: borrowRate0
docs: The lowest borrow rate in the first regime. Essentially the minimum
borrow rate possible for the reserve.

fields.name: borrowRate1
docs: The borrow rate at the transition point from the first to second regime.

fields.name: borrowRate2
docs: The borrow rate at the transition point from the second to thirs regime.

fields.name: borrowRate3
docs: The highest borrow rate in the third regime. Essentially the maximum
borrow rate possible for the reserve.

fields.name: minCollateralRatio
docs: The minimum allowable collateralization ratio for an obligation

fields.name: liquidationPremium
docs: The amount given as a bonus to a liquidator

fields.name: manageFeeCollectionThreshold
docs: The threshold at which to collect the fees accumulated from interest into
real deposit notes.

fields.name: manageFeeRate
docs: The fee rate applied to the interest payments collected

fields.name: loanOriginationFee
docs: The fee rate applied as interest owed on new loans

fields.name: reserved0
docs: unused

fields.name: confidenceThreshold
docs: Represented as a percentage of the Price
confidence values above this will not be accepted

fields.name: liquidationDexTradeMax
docs: The maximum token amount to allow in a single DEX trade when
liquidating assetr from this reserve as collateral.

fields.name: depositRewardMultiplier
docs: Multiplier that determines the fraction of reward points (by dividing over
sum of all multiplier for the market) allocated for deposit notes.

fields.name: borrowRewardMultiplier
docs: Multiplier that determines the fraction of reward points (by dividing over
sum of all multiplier for the market) allocated for loan notes.

types.name: Amount
docs: Represent an amount of some value (like tokens, or notes).
For units, possible values are TOKENS (0), DEPOSIT_NOTES (1), and LOAN_NOTES (2)

types.name: Rounding
docs: Specifies rounding integers up or down
